Well, I didn't actually go into or purchase from Burger King. As an Uber driver, I was parked in the parking lot waiting to get matched with my next passenger. In a very short amount of time, maybe 2 minutes, a white pickup backed into the parking spot next to mine at a fairly high rate of speed. The driver had his window down and by him reversing in, his door was right next to mine. My window was also open.  The gentleman looked remarkably similar to the Dade County, Florida hip-hop artist Trick Daddy but in his younger years. The resemblance was quite uncanny. The gentleman (who I shall refer to as Trick) asked me very directly what I was doing parked there. I told Trick that I was waiting on an Uber passenger. He chuckled and said that he thought that I was a Federal agent surveilling the 'hood. "Nope, Trick, just a boring uber driver." And as quickly as he had appeared he was gone. Trick love the kids. I took that opportunity to glance at my surroundings and noticed several other young men hanging and walking about looking curious as well at which time a second young man approached the vehicle. I grabbed my lifeless phone and said "Sorry, I gotta take this call" and made my exit (turning South onto a Northbound one-way street) and was out of there. I may return to this BK at some point but if I do, I think I'll opt for going into the lobby.

Most every morning before I go to work , I stop in this establishment for breakfast and coffee . There is usually a group of homeless people that are there buying breakfast and coffee as well . They are always respectful and try to maintain some dignity even though they are going through some difficult times . This morning I stopped by and they were refusing to open the doors for the public to sit down and enjoy their breakfast , only drive through business was being served , " AND IT HAD STARTED RAINING OUTSIDE " so I pulled out my phone and started recording the actions of the employees and manager . The manager sent 2 of them to confront me about recording the event , their response was a bit hateful and threatening , there were at least 4 emplyees and the so called Manager in there at this time , but they said that had to wait for another employee to show up before they would open the doors for anyone , and smart aleckly tried to intimidate me and said " WE DON'T CARE " !! Really Burger King ??   This reeks strongly of discrimination seeing as how most mornings there is is only 2-3 people working inside in the mornings . I for one thought that I would give you , Burger King , the chance to respond to these hateful actions before I send out this video on every social media outlet on the internet !!
